{"id":"hex-to-decimal","slug":"hex-to-decimal","name":"Hex to Decimal Converter","category":"converters","icon":"0x","description":"Convert hexadecimal (base-16) values to decimal. Used in programming and color codes.","tags":["hex","hexadecimal","decimal","converter","base-16"],"fields":[{"id":"hexDigits","label":"Hex value (as decimal — enter 0-15 per digit)","type":"number","defaultValue":255,"constraint":{"min":0}},{"id":"divided16","label":"÷ 16","type":"computed","precision":4},{"id":"mod16","label":"mod 16 (last digit)","type":"computed","precision":0}],"groups":[{"id":"inputs","label":"Number","fields":["hexDigits"]},{"id":"outputs","label":"Info","fields":["divided16","mod16"]}],"formulas":{"divided16":"hexDigits / 16","mod16":"mod(hexDigits, 16)"},"explanation":"## Hex to Decimal\n\n| Hex | Dec | Hex | Dec |\n|-----|-----|----|----|\n| 0 | 0 | 8 | 8 |\n| 1 | 1 | 9 | 9 |\n| A | 10 | B | 11 |\n| C | 12 | D | 13 |\n| E | 14 | F | 15 |\n\n**Example:** FF = 15×16 + 15 = **255**\n\n**Example:** 1A = 1×16 + 10 = **26**","examples":[{"label":"FF (255)","inputs":{"hexDigits":255}},{"label":"1A (26)","inputs":{"hexDigits":26}}]}
